  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Make the tapenade</strong></p>\n<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6.</p>\n<p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>garlic</strong>.</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>black olives</strong>,<strong> capers</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (don't like raw garlic? Go easy!), 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a<strong> food processor</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your<strong> tapenade</strong>. </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Seal the lamb</strong></p>\n<p>Pat the <strong>lamb rump</strong> dry with kitchen paper and season all over with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>.</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat.</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>lamb</strong> and cook for 4-5 minutes or until golden all over. </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cook the bulgur wheat</strong></p>\n<p>While the lamb is cooking, add the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> and <strong>sultanas</strong> to a pot with 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat.</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 15-18 minutes or until all the water is absorbed and the bulgur is tender with a slight bite.</p>\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving.</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Roast the lamb</strong></p>\n<p>Transfer the<strong> sealed lamb</strong> to a baking tray and put it in the oven for 20-25 minutes or until the lamb is pink and blushing.</p>\n<p>Once the lamb is cooked, transfer it to a plate and set aside to rest in a warm place for 5 minutes.</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1689.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
